# UK compliance domain rules

When touching tenancy, deposit, compliance certs, Right to Rent, or notices:

## HMO licensing

- A property with **5+ unrelated occupants from 2+ households** requires a mandatory HMO licence in England.
- Council additional/selective licensing covers smaller HMOs in some areas.
- Licence has an expiry; track via `compliance_items.type='hmo_licence'`.
- Operating unlicensed = unlimited fine + Rent Repayment Order (up to 12 months rent back).

See `docs/08-uk-compliance/hmo-licensing.md`.

## Right to Rent

- Mandatory in England for all adult occupants of a tenancy.
- Three valid methods: manual document, share code, IDSP.
- Time-limited rights need follow-up checks; track expiry.
- Stored as `compliance_items.type='right_to_rent'` with `tenancy_id`.
- Required before tenancy can activate.
- Failure to perform → up to £20,000 civil penalty per illegal occupant.

See `docs/08-uk-compliance/right-to-rent.md`.

## Deposit protection

- Max deposit = 5 weeks rent (annual rent < £50k) or 6 weeks (≥ £50k).
- Must be protected with DPS / MyDeposits / TDS within **30 days**.
- Prescribed Information must be given to tenant within 30 days.
- Failure = 1×–3× deposit penalty.

Track via `tenancies.deposit_scheme`, `deposit_reference`, `deposit_protected_at`, `prescribed_information_sent_at`.

See `docs/08-uk-compliance/deposit-protection.md`.

## Safety certificates

| Cert | Frequency |
|---|---|
| Gas Safety (CP12) | Annual |
| EICR | 5 years |
| EPC | 10 years (target C+ from 2028) |
| PAT | Recommended annual |
| Fire Risk Assessment | Annual (HMOs) |
| Legionella | Initial + on changes |
| Smoke alarm | Working at start of tenancy |
| CO alarm | In every room with combustion appliance |

Each gets a `compliance_items` row with `expires_at`. 60d / 30d / 7d / overdue reminders fire automatically.

See `docs/08-uk-compliance/safety-certificates.md`.

## Renters' Rights Bill

- **No Section 21** — never expose this option in any notice form.
- **Periodic tenancies by default** (`is_periodic=true`).
- **Rent increases**: max 1/year, 2-month notice via Section 13.
- **Tenant pets**: right to request; landlord cannot unreasonably refuse.
- **No DSS / no children** discrimination is illegal.

Encoded in `core/validation/tenancy.ts` and `core/utils/tenancy-rules.ts`. Server-side validation rejects illegal combinations.

See `docs/08-uk-compliance/renters-rights-bill.md`.

## Tax / MTD

- MTD ITSA mandatory: April 2026 for >£50k, April 2027 for >£30k landlord income.
- Capture income (`rent_payments`) and expenses (`expenses`) in pence.
- Provide quarterly + annual exports keyed to HMRC categories.

See `docs/08-uk-compliance/tax-and-mtd.md`.

## GDPR

- Identity docs (RTR) auto-delete 1 year post tenancy end.
- Tax data retained 7 years.
- Tenancy records retained 7 years.
- Audit log retained 2 years.
- All retention runs via Inngest cron.

See `docs/08-uk-compliance/gdpr-and-ico.md` + `docs/10-security/data-protection-gdpr.md`.

## When in doubt

The corresponding doc in `docs/08-uk-compliance/` is the source of truth. Don't infer rules from memory — UK property law is precise.
